|flags= |stock_os= |tp_firmware= |802dot11_protocols=bgn |default_ssid=WBR-6000 |default_ssid_regex=^WBR-6000$ |default_ip=192.168.0.1 |default_user=admin |default_pass=password |oui=00:11:6B |oui_eth=00:11:6B |default_ch= }} "YGB00A-1.6MM" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
"YGB10A-1.6MM" and a date code of '''0722''' (June 2007) is silkscreened on one particular production model unit's board. :This particular board is using all '''nichicon''' radial capacitors.
The device is on [http://download.level1.com/level1/member/marketingdocument/Broadband_and_ADSL_Router_Comparison_Table.xls this list].
The FCC ID printed on the label is P27-IP1006AA ([http://svn.dd-wrt.com:8000/ticket/321 on DD-WRT Trac]). The FCC ID in reality is P27IP1006AA.. which redirects to K7SF5D8231-4D.
The default SSID may be '''default'''.
The power adapter included with the device is a '''unbranded''' RHN-120100-1-1 (12V, 1A).
